# Index Page Styling Overrides

The index page has **inline theme styles** in `index.html` (the `<style>` block with `body.index-page` selectors) that override `main.css` for typography and other design.

- **When changing styles that must apply on the index page** (e.g. Experience section role titles, About highlights card titles, Extracurriculars titles, section-specific headings), add or update a **`body.index-page`** rule in that same inline `<style>` block so it wins over the theme.
- Use **`!important`** on those overrides when the theme already sets `!important` (e.g. `body.index-page h4` uses DM Sans with `!important`, so Experience role titles need `body.index-page #experience .experience-content h4 { ... !important }`).
- **Reference**: “Languages” in Skills uses: `font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.2px; line-height: 1.35`. Use this for any “match Languages” requests.
- Keep **main.css** updated too for non-index pages (e.g. about.html, experience.html, extracurriculars.html).
